criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

  -  Male Volunteers;

  -  Age ≥18 years and ≤45 years;

  -  BMI ≥20- ≤30 kg/m²

  -  No clinically significant screening observations

Exclusion Criteria:

  -  Female volunteers;

  -  Any history of significant cardiac, renal, neurologic, metabolic, pulmonary,
     gastrointestinal, chronic hepatic disease or any other disease which in the judgment
     of the Investigator would interfere with the study or confound the results;

  -  History of allergy or major allergic reactions considered to be clinically
     significant by the Investigator;

  -  Any screening assessment determined to be clinically significant by the Investigator;

  -  Donate blood within 60 days of screening or otherwise experienced blood loss >250 mL
     within the same period;
